\c[3]４階\c[0]：とってもビジネスなフロア
\c[3]３階\c[0]：もっとビジネスなフロア

message.en_US: Greetings, Seeker. Do you have any business with the mayor?
message.pt_BR: Saudações, Seeker. Você tem algum negócio com o prefeito?
message.zh_CN: 你好探索者。你找市长有事吗？<<A<<[CHANGED 2021/05/22]
message.ja_JP:
こんにちは、探索者さん。
市長になにかご用事が
おありですか？<<A<<[CHANGED 2021/05/22]
message.de_DE: Grüß dich, Seeker. Hast du etwas Geschäftliches mit dem Bürgermeister zu besprechen?<<A<<[CHANGED 2021/05/22]
message.zh_TW: 你好探索者。你找市長有事嗎？<<A<<[CHANGED 2021/05/22]

message.en_US: [nods]
message.pt_BR: [acena a cabeça]
message.ja_JP: [うなずく]<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: [nickt]

message.en_US: Are you sure?
message.pt_BR: Tem certeza?
message.zh_CN: 你确定吗？<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Bist du sicher?
message.zh_TW: 你確定嗎？<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: Do you perhaps want to proceed along the \c[3]Track of the Ancients\c[0]?
message.pt_BR: Você talvez queira prosseguir pela \c[3]Trilha dos Antigos\c[0]?
message.zh_CN: 你是想要询问如何继续\c[3]先祖之路\c[0]吗？<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/09/19]
message.ja_JP:
\c[3]いにしえの軌跡\c[0]をたどる旅を
進めたいんですよね？<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/09/19]
message.de_DE: Möchtest du vielleicht deine Reise auf dem \c[3]Pfad der Ahnen\c[0] fortsetzen?
message.zh_TW: 你是想要詢問如何繼續\c[3]先祖之路\c[0]嗎？<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/09/19]

message.en_US: [nods]
message.pt_BR: [acena a cabeça]
message.ja_JP: [うなずく]<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: [nickt]

message.en_US: Then you don't need to see the mayor.
message.pt_BR: Então você não precisa ver o prefeito.
message.zh_CN: 那么你不需要见市长。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP:
それなら、市長と会う
必要はありませんよ。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Dafür musst du ihn nicht sprechen.
message.zh_TW: 那麼你不需要見市長。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: Your next task as Seekers is to visit the temples in the \c[3]north of Gaia's Garden\c[0].
message.pt_BR: Sua próxima tarefa como Seeker é visitar os templos no \c[3]norte do Jardim de Gaia\c[0].
message.zh_CN: 作为探索者你的下一个任务是前往\c[3]盖亚花园北部\c[0]的神庙。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ko_KR: 시커로서의 다음 과제는 \c[3]가이아의 정원 북쪽\c[0]에 있는 사원에 방문하는 거거든.<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP:
あなたの探索者としての次の任務は、
\c[3]ガイアの園の北\c[0]にある神殿を
訪れることです。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Deine nächste Aufgabe besteht darin, die Tempel im \c[3]Norden von Gaias Garten\c[0] aufzusuchen.
message.zh_TW: 作為探索者你的下一個任務是前往\c[3]蓋亞花園北部\c[0]的神廟。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: All Seekers are free to enter those dungeons, no permission required!
message.pt_BR: Todos os Seekers são livres para entrar nessas masmorras, não é necessária permissão!
message.zh_CN: 所有的探索者都能随意进入那个地牢，不需要得到任何允许！<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ko_KR: 모든 시커는 허락 받지 않고도 그 던전에 자유롭게 들어갈 수 있어!<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP:
探索者は全員、許可を取らなくとも
自由にダンジョンに入ることができますよ！<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Allen Seekern ist es gestattet, sie ohne vorherige Erlaubnis zu betreten!
message.zh_TW: 所有的探索者都能隨意進入那個地牢，不需要得到任何允許！<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: Maybe also tell your fellow Seekers that they don't have to show up here. They just keep doing it.
message.pt_BR: Talvez também diga aos seus colegas Seekers que eles não precisam aparecer aqui. Eles apenas continuam fazendo isso.
message.zh_CN: 如果你碰到跟你一样的探索者，告诉他们继续做手上的事就行，不用来这里找市长。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ko_KR: 시커 동료들에게 이곳에 들르지 않아도 된다고 말해주는 게 어때? 그냥 하던대로 이어서 하면 된다고.<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP:
仲間の探索者さんにも、ここに
わざわざ来る必要はないと
伝えて頂けませんか。
ひっきりなしに来るので。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Sag das besser mal auch den anderen Seekern, damit sie nicht ständig zuerst hierherkommen. Das machen sie nämlich nach wie vor.
message.zh_TW: 如果你碰到跟你一樣的探索者，告訴他們繼續做手上的事就行，不用來這裡找市長。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: Why would they even want to see the mayor anyway?
message.pt_BR: Por que eles iriam querer ver o prefeito de qualquer maneira?
message.zh_CN: 他们来找市长也没什么太大用啊。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ko_KR: 대체 시장님을 왜 뵈려고 하는 걸까?<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP:
どうしてみなさん市長と
会いたがるんでしょうね？<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Warum wollen sie den Bürgermeister überhaupt sehen?
message.zh_TW: 他們來找市長也沒什麼太大用啊。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: It's not like he has any business with the track, right?
message.pt_BR: Não é como se ele tivesse algum negócio com a trilha, certo?
message.zh_CN: 市长对先祖之路的事根本没有太多了解。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ko_KR: 고대인의 길에 연관되어 있는 분도 아니시잖아?<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP:
市長は軌跡と
なにも関係ないでしょう？<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Der Pfad gehört doch gar nicht zu seinem Tagesgeschäft!
message.zh_TW: 市長對先祖之路的事根本沒有太多瞭解。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: Force of habit, I suppose?
message.pt_BR: Força do hábito, suponho?
message.zh_CN: 看来这是习惯成自然？<<A<<[CHANGED 2021/05/22]
message.ja_JP:
単なる俺たちの
癖ってことなのか？<<A<<[CHANGED 2021/05/22]
message.de_DE: Macht der Gewohnheit, wahrscheinlich.<<A<<[CHANGED 2021/05/22]
message.zh_TW: 看來這是習慣成自然？<<A<<[CHANGED 2021/05/22]

message.en_US: It seems the mayor of this town doesn't want to be involved in any of the Seeker's business!
message.pt_BR: Parece que o prefeito desta cidade não quer se envolver nos negócios dos Seekers!
message.zh_CN: 似乎市长不想让他的城市跟探索者的任务有任何牵连！<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ko_KR: 이 마을의 시장은 시커의 일에 연루되고 싶어 하지 않나 보군!<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP:
この街の市長は、
探索者と一切関わり合いに
なりたくないようだな！<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Scheint so, als ob der Bürgermeister hier nichts mit Seekern am Hut haben will!
message.zh_TW: 似乎市長不想讓他的城市跟探索者的任務有任何牽連！<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

task.en_US: No need to visit the \c[3]mayor\c[0] this time. You can just head straight to the temples of \c[3]Grand Krys'kajo\c[0]!
task.pt_BR: Não há necessidade de visitar o \c[3]prefeito\c[0] desta vez. Você pode simplesmente ir direto para os templos de \c[3]Grand Krys'kajo\c[0]!
task.zh_CN: 没必要去找\c[3]市长\c[0]了。直接前往\c[3]大凯斯卡罗\c[0]的神庙就好！<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
task.ko_KR: 이번에는 \c[3]시장님\c[0]을 뵈러 가지 않아도 됩니다. \c[3]그랜드 크리스카조\c[0]로 곧장 가면 됩니다!<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
task.ja_JP:
今回は\c[3]市長\c[0]に会う必要はないようだ。
まっすぐ\c[3]クリュス・カーヨ大神殿\c[0]に
向かおう！<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
task.de_DE: Ein \c[3]Bürgermeisterbesuch\c[0] ist nicht nötig. Der Weg zu den Tempeln des \c[3]Großen Krys'kajo\c[0] ist frei!
task.zh_TW: 沒必要去找\c[3]市長\c[0]了。直接前往\c[3]大凱斯卡羅\c[0]的神廟就好！<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: Greetings Seeker.
message.pt_BR: Saudações Seeker.
message.zh_CN: 你好啊，探索者。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP: こんにちは、探索者さん。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Grüß dich, Seeker.
message.zh_TW: 你好啊，探索者。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: If you want to proceed along the \c[3]Track of the Ancients\c[0] you don't need to see the mayor.
message.pt_BR: Se você quiser seguir pela \c[3]Trilha dos Antigos\c[0] não precisa ver o prefeito.
message.zh_CN: 如果你是为\c[3]先祖之路\c[0]而来，那么你没必要去见市长。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ko_KR: \c[3]고대인의 길\c[0]을 진행하고 싶어서라면, 시장님을 뵐 필요는 없어.<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP:
\c[3]いにしえの軌跡\c[0]を進みたいなら、
市長と会う必要はありませんよ。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Um deine Reise auf dem \c[3]Pfad der Ahnen\c[0] fortzusetzen, ist ein Bürgermeisterbesuch nicht vonnöten.
message.zh_TW: 如果你是為\c[3]先祖之路\c[0]而來，那麼你沒必要去見市長。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: Just visit the Temples in the \c[3]north of Gaia's Garden\c[0].
message.pt_BR: Basta visitar os Templos no \c[3]norte do Jardim de Gaia\c[0].
message.zh_CN: 直接前往\c[3]盖亚花园北部\c[0]的神庙就行了。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ko_KR: \c[3]가이아의 정원 북쪽\c[0]에 있는 사원에 가면 돼.<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.ja_JP:
\c[3]ガイアの園の北\c[0]にある
神殿を訪れてください。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: Suche einfach die Tempel im \c[3]Norden von Gaias Garten\c[0] auf.
message.zh_TW: 直接前往\c[3]蓋亞花園北部\c[0]的神廟就行了。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]

message.en_US: [nods]
message.pt_BR: [acena a cabeça]
message.ja_JP: [うなずく]<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/03/14]
message.de_DE: [nickt]

message.en_US: I'm sorry Seeker, but thanks to this noisy Shad I have my hands full with re-scheduling.
message.pt_BR: Desculpe, Seeker, mas graças a esse Shad barulhento, estou com as mãos cheias de reagendamentos.
message.ja_JP:
申し訳ありません、探索者さん。
でもこのうるさいシャッドのおかげで、
スケジュールを全て組み直さなくては
いけなくなったもので。<<A<<[CHANGED 2017/11/04]
message.ko_KR: 미안해, 시커. 하지만 이 샤드 때문에 약속을 다시 잡아야 하느라 바빠서 말이야.<<A<<[CHANGED 2017/11/16]
message.zh_CN: 抱歉探索者，但是因为那些吵闹的沙德人我现在真的腾不出手。<<A<<[CHANGED 2017/12/12]
message.de_DE: Tut mir leid, Seeker, aber dank diesen Schreihälsen hier habe ich gerade alle Hände voll zu tun.
message.zh_TW: 抱歉探索者，但是因為那些吵鬧的沙德人我現在真的騰不出手。<<A<<[CHANGED 2017/12/12]

message.en_US: Hello Seeker, the Mayor is free if you want to visit him.
message.pt_BR: Olá Seeker, o prefeito está livre se você quiser visitá-lo.
message.ja_JP:
こんにちは、探索者さん。
市長は今手が空いていますので、
面会したければご自由にどうぞ。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/09/19]
message.ko_KR: 안녕, 시커. 지금은 시장님을 뵈러 가도 돼.<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/09/19]
message.zh_CN: 探索者你好，市长已有空闲，你可以去见他了。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/09/19]
message.de_DE: Hallo, Seeker. Der Bürgermeister hat jetzt Zeit, falls du ihn sehen willst.
message.zh_TW: 探索者你好，市長已有空閒，你可以去見他了。<<A<<[CHANGED 2018/09/19]

message.en_US: Cool, thanks to this weird Shad I now have to wait for my appointment with the mayor.
message.pt_BR: Legal, graças a esse Shad esquisito agora tenho que esperar meu encontro com o prefeito.
message.ja_JP:
最高だよ。あの妙なシャッドのおかげで、
市長と約束していたのに待たされるんだから。<<A<<[CHANGED 2017/11/04]
message.ko_KR: 참나, 이 이상한 샤드 때문에 시장님과의 만남을 기다려야 하잖아?<<A<<[CHANGED 2017/11/16]
message.zh_CN: 多亏了那些奇怪的沙德人，我现在还得等预约才能见到市长了。<<A<<[CHANGED 2017/12/12]
message.de_DE: Toll, dank dieser verrückten Shad darf ich jetzt auf meinen Termin mit dem Bürgermeister warten.
message.zh_TW: 多虧了那些奇怪的沙德人，我現在還得等預約才能見到市長了。<<A<<[CHANGED 2017/12/12]
